Job Description:

Airbus Commercial Aircraft is looking for a Machine Learning Engineer to join our Artificial Intelligence for Systems Team (ARTIST) based in Toulouse, France or Hamburg, Germany. 

You will join the Data Management & AI team within the Data-Driven Services & Aircraft Maintenance Community. Your primary focus will be on developing AI/Data Science technology bricks to make the link between model development and industrialization for the aircraft system design, with an initial assignment centered on embedded aircraft systems for computer vision applications (Cockpit).

To discover more about our activities, watch our video:ATTOL: Autonomous Taxiing, Take-Off and Landing test flight.

Your working environment:

Global capital of aeronautics and European capital for space research, Toulouse is a dynamic city in the southwest of France served by an international airport. Ideally located between the Mediterranean sea and the Atlantic ocean and close to the Pyrenees mountains, it offers plenty of options for outdoor activities!

How we care for you:

Financial rewards: Attractive salary, agreements on success and profit sharing schemes, employee savings plan abounded by Airbus and employee stock purchase plan on a voluntary basis.

Work / Life Balance: Extra days-off for special occasions, holiday transfer option, a Staff council offering many social, cultural and sport activities and other services.

Wellbeing / Health: Complementary health insurance coverage (disability, invalidity, death). Depending on the site: health services center, concierge services, gym, carpooling application.

Individual development: Great upskilling opportunities and development prospects with unlimited access to +10.000 e-learning courses to develop your employability, certifications, expert career path, accelerated development programmes, national and international mobility.

At Airbus, we support you to work, connect and collaborate more easily and flexibly. Wherever possible, we foster flexible working arrangements to stimulate innovative thinking.

Your challenges:

Develop software solutions for advanced AI targeting aircraft products and ways of working, with a focus on embedded systems for computer vision (Cockpit).

Productionize: turn experimental code into production-ready pipelines optimized for embedded systems

Ensure communication and alignment with internal and external stakeholders, including Programs, R&T, Engineering, and IT.

Collaborate: Partner with Data Scientists and aircraft system engineers on model architecture and implementation 

Contribute to the vision and strategy for AI-based solutions and improvements for Aircraft Systems, Services, and Ways of Working.

Coach students and engineers around AI applications, data-driven mindset, and agile ways of working.

Your boarding pass:

Master degree in Data Science, Artificial Intelligence or equivalent.

Minimum of 1 year experience in development of solutions based on Advanced Statistics, Machine Learning & Deep Learning methods, preferably around computer vision.â€‹

Technical Expertise:

# Experience in industrialization and implementation of AI solutions in a production environment. Expertise in Machine Learning algorithms & tools linked to supervised, un supervised, and reinforcement learning. Knowledge and experience in computer vision applications is a big plus. # Experience with MLOps/DevOps methods and cloud infrastructure # Proficiency in development environments & programming languages like Python, PySpark, Linux Shell Scripting, and NoSQL databases.

English Negotiation level

Knowledge of French or German would be a plus.

This position requires a security clearance or will require being eligible for clearance by the recognized authorities.

Not a 100% match? No worries! Airbus supports your personal growth with customized development solutions.
